title: Normal Human BP9 EXO
extract_protocol_ch1: Exosome prep (cells were removed from plasma by centrifugation for 30 min at 2,000 x g, 4°C., followed by removal of cellular debris by centrifugation of supernatant for 45 min at 12,000 x g, 4°C. Exosomes were pelleted by high-speed centrifugation 110,000 x g, 4°C for 70 min, and pellets were washed and resuspended in 1X PBS. Exosomes were depleted of lipoproteins by FPLC fractionation, and all fractions larger than LDL were collected and concentrated, Qiagen miRNAEasy Kit Total RNA isolation
label_protocol_ch1: 20ng of total RNA was reverse transcribed with MegaPlex RT-Pools (A&B) (43 cycles), followed by preamplification using MegaPlex PreAmp primers (pool A&B) with PreAmp Master Mix, samples were diluted 1:4 with 1X TE pH8.0 and 10uL of samples was diluted 1:100 with H2O and 2X PCR Master MIx
hyb_protocol: Individual Taqman Probes & Primers, Tiled-Low Density Array
contact_department: National Heart, Lung and Blood Institute
